parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel vapor control valve can cause the engine check light to illuminate, leading to potential engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions. If left unchecked, it can also lead to more serious problems, such as engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The engine check light comes on and stays on
the vehicle experiences decreased engine performance
the vehicle has decreased fuel efficiency
